      <div type="apparatus" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
        <head>Apparatus</head>
        <p>The monument appears to be complete below; it must be assumed that it originally stood on another feature on which the last line of the epigram was inscribed.</p>
        <p>l.8. <foreign lang="grc">ΤΕΙΡΕΕΙ</foreign>, corrected by Cormack and Robert.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="translation" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab part="N">He did not die, nor did he see the stream of Acheron, but in Olympus Asclepiodotus is among the stars—he who also built many splendid things for his motherland <gap dim="bottom" extent="1" unit="line" reason="lost"/></ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>For Asclepiodotus see also <xref type="iAph" n="053" evaluate="all" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" from="ROOT">53</xref>; see discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" evaluate="all" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" from="ROOT" n="V.8">V.8</xref>.</p>
      <p>For the funerary epigram see discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" evaluate="all" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" from="ROOT" n="IX.15">IX.15</xref>, <xref type="eAla-text" evaluate="all" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" from="ROOT" n="IX.19">IX.19</xref>.</p></div>

      <div type="history" n="locations" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform"><head>Locations</head><p>Found: <rs type="findspot">Village: reused supporting a pillar of a verandah, in a house subsequently demolished.</rs>. Original location: <rs type="orig-location">Unknown.</rs>. Last recorded location: <rs type="last-location">Museum.</rs>. </p></div>

      

      

